# Dependencies

Some services require other services to run first.

Example:

```text
Print Spooler
      │
      ▼
RPC Service
```

If RPC is stopped:

```text
Print Spooler
Cannot Start
```

Windows checks dependencies before starting a service.

---

### View Dependencies

```powershell
Get-Service Spooler |
Select -ExpandProperty ServicesDependedOn
```

Or

```powershell
Get-Service Spooler |
Format-List *
```

---

### Check Dependent Services

```powershell
Get-Service Spooler |
Select -ExpandProperty DependentServices
```

